parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame and Axle Issues in Thor Tahoe Toy Haulers
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frame and axle issues can cause the vehicle to sway excessively, leading to loss of control, tire blowouts, and accidents, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle sways excessively while driving
the vehicle drifts into the median or other lanes
tire blowouts
body damage
and difficulty maintaining control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective frame structure can cause safety issues, such as difficulty opening doors, uneven floor, and increased risk of tire blowouts, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The frame is out of square
making it difficult to open doors
the floor sags
tires blow out easily
and windows and vents open on their own due to vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A warped or flawed windshield can obstruct the driver's view, causing blurry vision, especially in sunlight, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield is warped
has flaws on the glass
appears wavy when driving in sunlight
and road signs and objects appear blurry.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause inconvenience, distraction, and potentially affect vehicle safety, as the driver may be unable to access important information or operate the vehicle's audio and navigation systems.
symptoms: The navigation system
radio
and CD player suddenly stop working
the screen goes black
and the system becomes stuck on one radio station
with no other functions accessible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden and unintended acceleration from slow speeds can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries to occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates forward from slow speeds (<5mph) without warning
throwing occupants back into their seats
after a brief delay (a few seconds) following accelerator pedal input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to lose stability, leading to loss of control, accidents, or rollovers, especially when driving over rough terrain or hard bumps.
symptoms: The "Running Gear Fault" or "Workshop" warning message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle's air suspension system fails to maintain proper ride height
the vehicle's handling and stability are compromised
the vehicle may experience sudden drops or bounces
and in extreme cases
the vehicle may roll over.
